Expanded Widget â€” Explained (English + Marathi)
ðŸ”¹ What is Expanded Widget? (English)

Expanded is a Flutter widget used inside Row, Column, or Flex.
It helps a child widget take up the available remaining space.

âœ“ Why do we use Expanded? (à¤•à¤¾ à¤µà¤¾à¤ªà¤°à¤¤à¥‹?)
ðŸ‘‰ English

To distribute space between widgets

To avoid overflow

To make responsive UI

To control space using flex

import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(MaterialApp(
    home: Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: Text(
          "Container Example",
          style: TextStyle(fontSize: 22, color: Colors.purple),
        ),
      ),

      body: Row(
        mainAxisAlignment: MainAxisAlignment.center,
        children: [

         Expanded(
           child: Container(
            width: 50,
            height: 50,
            color: Colors.red,
          ),),
Expanded(
  child:Container(
            width: 30,
            height: 30,
            color: Colors.green,
          ),
),

          Expanded(
            flex:6,//flex value to take more space
            child: Container(
              height: 30,
              color: const Color.fromARGB(255, 147, 170, 147),
            ),
          ),
        ],
      ),
    ),
  ));
}
